						<summary>

						<p>On top of the slab. [No. 1575] First Face.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1638 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that the gharaḍa (garuḍa)gaṁbha of the Māraṭēśvara temple was set up by Līngaṇṇa, son of <hi rend="italic">gāṇigara</hi> Jābi-Seṭṭi.</p>						

						<p>It is dated śaka 1559, Īśvara, Māgha (A)māse. It corresponds to 1638 A.D., February 3, Saturday.</p>						

						</summary>
